data.title: what volusia has been missing
data.text: By far the best Authentic Spanish food I have had dine out. just like a home cooked family dinner. Everything made fresh when you order. Mom and pops feeling with great music, atmosphere , dominos , owners on spot to make you feel at home. GREAT GREAT just what our community ity needed

data.title: One word "Awesome"
data.text: My wife's co-worker recommended this restaurant to us. When we arrived the restaurant owner  greeted us as if we were family. The service was excellent, the portions were really generous and the prices unbeatable. If your looking for true Puerto Rican food then this is the place to eat.

data.title: Yummy!
data.text: We have been here quite a few times and absolutely loved it.  Everything has always been tasty, the service has always been great... I definitely recommend it to anyone.  We've always had delivery and it has always been prompt and they have been very friendly!

data.title: Made to order... Coconut Icee is amazing!
data.text: We tried multiple items on the Saturday before Easter. Everything was great other then the potato ball. It wasn't that great and was cold in the center. The beef and cheese empanadas were the best I've ever had! Great prices and the owners are very nice and talkative. We need a good place like this owned by good people in Deltona.

data.title: Incredible highway stop!
data.text: We picked this spot while driving on the highway because of its perfect score for reviews. Everthing is made from scratch and so worth the wait. Sandwiches on plantains, amazing!! Cubano was the best! My dish was made vegetarian and was sooooo good! Dont remember what it was called but it was like an open face plantain sandwich with salad on top and cheese with a great hot sauce.

data.title: Excellent food and superb warm friendly atmosphere!
data.text: The Double Six Diner is a nice cozy Puerto Rican-Spanish style food restaurant where you feel like you are back home, wherever home is; NY, NJ, Philadelphia or PR. You need to try the "Yuca rellenas" and the Canoas, excellent choices for a quick snack or meal. The food overall is great, fresh and very tasty. Johnny and Brenda make you feel like home and they also support the community sponsoring a Senior Softball League team. Great people, great food! It is my favorite place to get a quick snack and a good meal!

data.title: ICEE A WINNER!
data.text: After checking out Trip Advisor for the best ranked restaurant in Deltona, this place is ranked number one. The restaurant has around 8 to 10 tables. It has that diner feel. Spanish music is playing the whole time while you eat.  They describe their food as being New York- Puerto Rican. I'm not too familiar with this cuisine so I decided on ordering a Cuban sandwich. It's definitely different than most Cubans with what I believe is shredded roast pork. It's very tasty and filling as I only ate about 3/4th's of it. Also on Trip Advisor a lot of people were raving about their icee's saying how good they were and I must say they are completely right. I tried their strawberry- lemonade and I was close to trying another one because they're so good but I was too full.  I was talking to the owners son a little bit while I was eating and he was super friendly and helpful. He said they have been open since Halloween and that the restaurant keeps getting busier and busier.

data.title: Cold Cuban sandwich
data.text:
I stopped by one day after work and ordered a Cuban sandwich you to try them out. I didn't get around to eating it till two or three hours later. So it's cold it could be a hit or miss.
it was over the top good. 
It was so good I went back to get a second one for my wife.
We enjoyed the service and the meal.

data.title: It's what you've been looking for!
data.text: First, I found this great place by searching other trip advisor reviews - so many people simply can't be wrong. Juan treats you like your family and food is top notch. The place is clean, open and inviting. True family businesses show themselves for the gems they usually are and this spot is no exception! If you don't get some shaved ice while your there, you my good sir/ma'am are then a fool. This is on the top of a long list of affordable home cooked magical meals I've ever had. Well done Juan and family.

data.title: Magnificent food and atmosphere
data.text: Best food and place in Deltona. My #1 Restaurant from now on. By the way, don't forget to try the ices, this place is the only who sells the original ices from NY and it's homemade by the owner. Great place, food, music and humble owners.

data.title: The best in Deltona!
data.text: The food excellent in taste and great price. wow! Service exvellent! Friendly and well welcomed by the owners.

data.title: Speechless!
data.text: When I say this place had me speechless when I tasted the food, I mean it literally left me speechless. I have lived all over FL for the past ten years and never have I ever encountered a restaurant whose food is so authentic and so delicious it leaves you hungry for more even after you are full. The food is literally homemade as the business owners make it themselves and serve you more than ever expected. Really cheap for the amount of food served. Excellent quality of service from the moment we walked in. The owners came out and got to know us on a one on one basis. They really took us back to our home NYC. I give this place my highest recommendation and I dare say that this place is the BEST Puerto Rican restaurant in the Deltona area and I dare say also the BEST in Central Florida.

data.title: Terrific food made with lots of love!!
data.text: What a wonder family restaurant!! Everything on the menu is fresh, made to order!! The chicken was tender and seasoned to perfection! The atmosphere is so fun and full of laughter..you feel like your a part of the family that owns and runs it!!

data.title: Excellent and very tasty
data.text: Tony and his wife Brenda are very personable and the food was just like momma used to make it. The bistec con cebolla was tasty and tender and moist. The rice and beans like moms. Will be back with friends and family in tow. Yummy!!!

data.title: Great food and service!
data.text: Wow! Me and my husband had dinner tonite there and the food was so flavorable. The people who work there are clearly in the right business. I will definitely be spreading the news about this awesome spot.
